Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getGenerateViaMode(25.10)                            getGenerateViaMode(25.10)

Name
       getGenerateViaMode  - Displays the information about the specified set-
       GenerateViaMode parameter in the Innovus log file and  in  the  Innovus
       console

Syntax
       getGenerateViaMode

       [-help]

       [-auto]

       [-ndr_only {true|false}]

       [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Displays the information about the specified setGenerateViaMode parame-
       ter  in  the  Innovus log file and in the Innovus console. Displays the
       following information:

              * Option name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the  software  displays  information
       for all of the setGenerateViaMode mode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each getGenerateViaMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getGenerateViaMode.

       -auto  Enables auto via generation when design is loaded.

       -nonDefault
              Displays the current settings which are not default settings.

       -ndr_only {true|false}
              Generates vias for non default rules only.

              Default: false

       -quiet Displays the current settings in Tcl list format only.

Example
       The following command gives the values of -auto and  -ndr_only  parame-
       ters that are set using the setGenerateViaMode:

       > getGenerateViaMode

       -auto true # bool, default=false, user setting

       -ndr_only true # bool, default=false, user setting

       {auto true} {ndr_only true}

Related Information
